==Old English==

===Etymology===
West Germanic, of unknown origin: cognate with Old Frisian [[knecht]], Old Saxon [[knecht]], Old High German [[kneht]] (German [[Knecht]], Dutch [[knecht]]).

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /knɪɣt/

===Noun===
'''cniht''' ''m'' (''pl'' '''cnihtas''')
# a [[boy]] or [[youth]]
# a male servant or attendant
# a male of high military rank, ranking below a [[baron]], usually previously having worked as a [[page]] or [[squire]]

===Descendants===
*English [[knight]] / [[Knight]]

